06178nam a22008415i 9783035623260DE-B159720221107062033.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221107t20222022sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2022942558  a97830356232607 a10.1515/97830356232602doi  a(DE-B1597)571563  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0050702bisacsh04a72000aArchitects and Engineers :bModes of Cooperation in the Interwar Period, 1919–1939 /ced. by Roland May. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (160 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aKulturelle und technische Werte historischer Bauten ;v700tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tSome Introductory Remarks on Architects, Engineers, Modes of Cooperation between Them, and the Importance of the Interwar Period for All This -- tLooking Back on Architect and Engineer -- tEngineering Belgian Interwar Modernisms Some Examples of Architect-Engineer-Contractor Relations -- t«Architect, do not imitate the forms of technology but learn the method of the structural engineer!» The Cooperation of Russian Avant-Garde Architects and Engineers -- tThe Relationship between the Modern Movement and Civil Engineering in Weimar Germany -- tArchitect and Engineer around the World, 1919–39 An Exploration in Photographs -- tItalian Modernisms Structure and Architecture in the Interwar Period -- tNot Just the Dirty Work Architects and Engineers in Britain between the Wars -- tEduardo Torroja and Architects, 1926–36 -- tThe ‹Queen of Engineering› The Engineer Max Mayer’s ‹Science of Management› and its Impact on German Modernist Architectural Design around 19300 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn den ersten Jahrzehnten des 20. Jahrhunderts galt die Arbeitsweise von Bauingenieuren weithin als vorbildlich für die künftigen Architekten. Ihre Bedeutung für die zeitgenössischen Architekturbewegungen wurde hingegen kaum thematisiert. Bis heute warten selbst grundlegende Fragen zu Kooperationen, Konkurrenzen und Konflikten zwischen diesen beiden Schwesterdisziplinen auf Antworten. Dieser Band versammelt Beiträge internationaler Wissenschaftler zur Zusammenarbeit von Architekten und Bauingenieuren in verschiedenen Ländern während der Zwischenkriegszeit. Er bietet Einblicke in nationale Besonderheiten, stellt neue Überlegungen zu Wesen, Charakter und Bedeutung solcher gemeinsamen Anstrengungen bietet und eröffnet so spannende neue Perspektiven auf die moderne Baukultur in Europa und darüber hinaus  aIn the first decades of the 20th century, civil engineers were widely seen as a role model for future architects. Their role within the contemporary architecture movements, however, was hardly discussed. To this day, even fundamental questions about collaborations, rivalries, or conflicts between the two sister disciplines still await answers. This volume brings together contributions by international scholars on the cooperation between architects and civil engineers in various countries in the interwar period. By offering both insights into national peculiarities and new reflections on the general nature, character, and significance of such joint efforts, it opens exciting new perspectives on the modern building culture of Europe and beyond.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aARCHITECTURE / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh1 aDevos, Rika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHernando de la Cuerda, Rafael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIori, Tullia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMay, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMay, Roland, eeditor